Aedeagus (
Fig. 3
) long and slender, step-like curved at basal third, with distinct sagittal aileron and apical portion attenuated and weakly S-curved, with a small knobbed apex. Basal orifice clearly emarginate. Endophallus armature well-developed, pairwise, the right piece long, heavily sclerotized and markedly projecting beyond apical orifice while the left one much shorter, less distinctly outlined, rounded apically. Parameres slender, curved, each bearing 3–4 apical setae; left one clearly longer, with small but distinct ventral apophysis.
